    "Glaucoma drainage devices have been shown to be an effective option for managing complex glaucoma cases, providing long-term IOP controlThe patient has silicone oil-induced glaucoma which is a known complication after vitrectomy with silicone oil tamponade.",
    "Given that the glaucoma is medication resistant, surgical intervention is likely the next step.",
    "This could involve:1.",
